Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.50,0:01:47.49,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,270)}Ep. 43 - Passed By
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.69,0:02:06.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My sister Lucy hadn't been home for two nights now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.63,0:02:11.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We looked for her as best we could,\Nbut couldn't trace where she went.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.96,0:02:16.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And then, when I woke up the morning,\NLittle was gone too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.89,0:02:19.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think he went to look for Lucy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.11,0:02:20.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.29,0:02:24.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little is an intelligent dog,\Nso he might actually pull it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.40,0:02:26.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's be good...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.02,0:02:29.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, why won't Lucy come home?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.30,0:02:30.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad shouldn't have done that!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.90,0:02:31.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.91,0:02:35.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad shouldn't have sold our sheep, Snowflake.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.46,0:02:39.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But you know he didn't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.01,0:02:42.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If dad would've kept her, we'd go completely broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.38,0:02:44.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad could solve it by working more!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.73,0:02:46.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not with an injured leg!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.29,0:02:49.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It already healed by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.21,0:02:52.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't understand\Nbecause you've not been home in a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.81,0:02:55.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,but dad is being an awful layabout lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.22,0:02:58.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All he does is drinking all day long!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.14,0:02:59.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All day long?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.61,0:03:03.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, precisely. Even after his leg healed,\Nhe didn't go out to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.53,0:03:05.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's how we became so poor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.54,0:03:09.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Before, dad used to barely drink any alcohol at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.30,0:03:13.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy running away from home and all is dad's fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.00,0:03:15.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.70,0:03:17.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You pity him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.50,0:03:21.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad was robbed of the last fractions of hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.69,0:03:26.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He came to believe\Nthat he won't ever get to own a farm in his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.80,0:03:33.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we came all the way to the faraway Southern Australia was to build a marvelous farm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.31,0:03:36.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, that prospect seems to be as distant as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.60,0:03:42.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But one should never give up on hoping, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.53,0:03:44.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.41,0:03:46.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know! You go say that to dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.28,0:03:48.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That things are only starting now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.87,0:03:51.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll definitely get our chance to own a plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.51,0:03:53.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.70,0:03:56.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I won't criticize dad anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.19,0:04:00.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Dad repents it himself more than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.15,0:04:15.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.39,0:04:18.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hit it again just as it healed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.21,0:04:26.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if only a cup...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.59,0:04:33.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where's dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.71,0:04:35.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In the next room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.79,0:04:42.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.76,0:04:45.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you drinking from the very morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:50.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, no... It's that I just hit my leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.62,0:04:52.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'll stop. I won't drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.78,0:04:54.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is Little still away?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.91,0:04:55.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.90,0:04:58.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So Little disappeared as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.80,0:05:00.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's probably searching for Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.80,0:05:02.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We also have to go look for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:04.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.59,0:05:07.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, you wanted to drink instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.71,0:05:11.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm told you've been spending your days drinking lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.21,0:05:12.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.70,0:05:15.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've been saving a little of my salary,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:18.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,but even that won't be enough\Nto buy Snowflake back, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.15,0:05:20.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt it. I got good money for Snowflake.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.93,0:05:24.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But thinking about it now,\NI probably shouldn't have sold her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:29.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father, even if you didn't have a single chance\Nto get a plot up to now,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.29,0:05:32.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I still think it's way too soon to throw away the hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.60,0:05:37.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father, one day you'll get your land\Nand build a marvelous farm on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.31,0:05:41.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll also put my every effort into it\Nand even Clara is going to do her best...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.80,0:05:43.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.36,0:05:46.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Clara? You're going out?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.42,0:05:49.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Ben, I'm reassured now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.01,0:05:50.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You've become such a responsible man!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.99,0:05:52.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.01,0:05:54.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben, Clara.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.06,0:05:58.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It seems I've been causing you\Na lot of unnecessary worry, haven't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.70,0:06:01.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've always put my unwavering trust in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.20,0:06:04.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that if you keep drinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.09,0:06:06.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.39,0:06:09.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben gave me quite a scolding for that just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.42,0:06:11.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't scold you, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.52,0:06:17.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After meeting nothing but disappointment and worry in these lands, I ended up developing a drinking habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.70,0:06:22.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see now. Ben put it in no uncertain terms for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.19,0:06:24.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I threw away every trace of hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.19,0:06:28.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The hope of building a marvelous farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.71,0:06:32.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Saying things so faint-hearted is not like you at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.30,0:06:38.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I also said that we'll still have a chance\Nto acquire as much land as we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.22,0:06:43.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly! Father, don't let the flame of hope die out.\NFor family and for everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.05,0:06:46.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I'm lucky to have such a wonderful family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.30,0:06:49.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it's missing one of its members now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.72,0:06:51.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Lucy-May...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.50,0:06:53.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where could she be by now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.10,0:06:55.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't she return?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.80,0:06:56.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.39,0:07:01.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This remorse from selling Snowflake is unbearable!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.99,0:07:16.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, why are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.23,0:07:18.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Back when your dad was taking Snowflake away,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.91,0:07:22.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I should've stopped him,\Nthen nothing of this would've happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:24.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.86,0:07:29.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.09,0:07:31.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.10,0:07:35.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your father is still home, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.07,0:07:37.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. They're awaiting your arrival.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.89,0:07:40.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is something haunting me since yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.45,0:07:44.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have a single clue\Nabout how we should look for Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.04,0:07:49.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Combing through the city of Adelaide\Nfrom one edge to another is our only option.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.19,0:07:51.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be totally impossible with just three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:54.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, we just gotta find some leads.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.91,0:07:57.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.69,0:08:00.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why is Lucy nowhere to be seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.92,0:08:12.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Mr. Pettywell is going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.89,0:08:17.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.93,0:08:18.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.92,0:08:23.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone forgot about it,\Nbut little Tob actually said he saw Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.33,0:08:24.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:29.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's just something Tob said,\Nwe didn't make much of it and soon forgot about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.51,0:08:32.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But if what Tob said was true...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.11,0:08:35.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,About Lucy looking at him from the carriage window?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.43,0:08:37.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Without saying anything, not even smiling at him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.70,0:08:40.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's a bizarre story for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.00,0:08:44.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But if it {\i1}was{\i0} true after all,\Nthat's the only lead on Lucy we currently have.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.89,0:08:55.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Tob.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.92,0:08:56.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.18,0:08:59.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You know Mr. Pettywell's carriage, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.22,0:09:02.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Was it that kind of carriage?\NThe one Lucy rode.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.85,0:09:04.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was even bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:06.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even bigger? How much bigger?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.48,0:09:10.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This big!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.78,0:09:17.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, did that carriage have any paintwork on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.09,0:09:20.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.51,0:09:25.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Tob. Are you sure the girl in carriage was Lucy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.31,0:09:29.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That was Lucy for sure. I'm certain!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.10,0:09:32.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, why did she pretend not to know you\Nwhen she saw you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.90,0:09:34.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.30,0:09:36.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't suppose it could've been someone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.39,0:09:39.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No way! It was our Lucy, I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.72,0:09:42.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why would Lucy pretend she doesn't know you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.93,0:09:45.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Because... Because that's what happened! 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.24,0:09:51.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tob, no need to cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.13,0:09:54.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that girl just resembled Lucy a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.01,0:09:57.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In a place such as Adelaide, there should be\Nat least one girl resembling her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.80,0:10:02.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And what if she suddenly fell ill, developed\Na high fever and became inert to everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.11,0:10:04.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Fell ill, huh?
Comment: 0,0:10:14.05,0:10:16.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.05,0:10:21.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When examining her from the outside,\NI can't seem to find anything out of the ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.30,0:10:25.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That said, she's still unable to regain her memory...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.47,0:10:27.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose she is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.50,0:10:31.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's the first such case in my practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.70,0:10:33.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you feel unwell somehow, Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.30,0:10:35.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.01,0:10:36.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.93,0:10:37.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.72,0:10:41.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Am I going to stay forever like this,\Nunable to regain my memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.34,0:10:43.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I wouldn't consider that as a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.70,0:10:48.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, I want to find out who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.34,0:10:49.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.87,0:10:52.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know, I know. It'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.29,0:10:54.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your memory will totally return one of these days!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.95,0:10:55.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It'd better.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.30,0:10:57.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.61,0:11:01.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I understand how you feel,\Nbut you shouldn't rush yourself so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.49,0:11:04.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're not at all troubled\Nby your current position, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.90,0:11:06.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.41,0:11:10.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, you can think of this place\Nas of your own home for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.01,0:11:11.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And of me as of your own mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.82,0:11:12.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.30,0:11:17.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to have taken matters pretty far, madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.70,0:11:19.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.06,0:11:22.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't get it?\NLetting her call you mother and all...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.41,0:11:24.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I don't mind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.13,0:11:27.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I really think she's an adorable girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.30,0:11:28.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.73,0:11:31.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, her parents haven't showed up yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.84,0:11:33.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We can't count on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.43,0:11:35.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How would they know she's here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.39,0:11:37.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.34,0:11:41.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But then, her parents are probably desperately looking for her now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.06,0:11:43.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.36,0:11:47.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But then, what should we possibly do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.30,0:11:48.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.53,0:11:58.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Prospero! Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.99,0:12:01.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How does she look, doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:05.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Still no progress?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.40,0:12:08.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Sylvia, I'm going out now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.24,0:12:09.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.54,0:12:11.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To visit the Duke of York in his mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.31,0:12:13.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He returned from England yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.46,0:12:15.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.22,0:12:18.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please give my regards to Duke and his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:19.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.92,0:12:24.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can be free now, Emily.\NHow about you go play in the garden?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.80,0:12:25.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.90,0:12:56.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Stop near that carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.50,0:12:57.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.00,0:13:06.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mr. Princeton!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.39,0:13:10.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going out?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.00,0:13:11.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.12,0:13:12.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It seems I'm in luck today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.81,0:13:16.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If I'd had come just a little later,\NI wouldn't be able to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.45,0:13:17.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you need something from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.93,0:13:21.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly! I've been meaning to resume yesterday's talks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.01,0:13:22.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Resume yesterday's talks?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.79,0:13:23.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.41,0:13:24.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So how about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.90,0:13:28.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Will you please sell your farm near Gawler to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.92,0:13:31.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty sure I already gave you\Nmy unambiguous refusal yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.50,0:13:35.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And I said that I'm not giving up that easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.63,0:13:37.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My answer remains the same today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.73,0:13:41.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not selling that farm.\NNow or later, I have no such intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.07,0:13:42.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please take your leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.51,0:13:44.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've prepared a whole 2000 pounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.78,0:13:46.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You just can't understand, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.82,0:13:48.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a matter of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.62,0:13:49.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.30,0:13:50.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.56,0:13:53.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was about to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.77,0:13:55.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Princeton!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.11,0:13:57.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we can depart now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.41,0:14:01.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not giving up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.99,0:14:04.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting here. Mr. Princeton!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.22,0:14:28.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Adelaide Bridge...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.11,0:14:36.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh shoot! I've forgotten something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.59,0:14:41.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Max! I'm sorry, but could you\Nturn back to the mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.32,0:14:49.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? He's back!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.30,0:14:56.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I probably overdid it, offering 2000 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.70,0:15:01.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well so be it. I can definitely resell\Na farm like that to another with a way bigger tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.07,0:15:18.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well now, it seems you finally came\Nto see the reason, Mr. Princeton?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.10,0:15:19.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.23,0:15:24.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please rest assured. You didn't mishear it\Nwhen I offered you a whopping 2000 pounds for it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.59,0:15:27.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better leave at once, Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.02,0:15:29.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I returned for another reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.59,0:15:31.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:43.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No pecking! It hurts. No means no!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.31,0:15:46.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.69,0:15:51.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can't peck me. I don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.94,0:15:58.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? What's wrong, guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.67,0:16:02.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! So it was you, Prospero?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.09,0:16:06.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see. She's a girl with an adoration for animals?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.10,0:16:09.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She said it's something she realized about herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.00,0:16:14.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's curious how she can't even remember her name,\Nbut managed to realize her animal-loving nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.50,0:16:15.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What a good child she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.61,0:16:19.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you not to come near, you naughty child?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.43,0:16:23.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It appears you've come to dote sincerely on this child.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.90,0:16:24.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.83,0:16:25.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.00,0:16:34.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, there was something\NI needed to talk to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.10,0:16:35.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, doctor, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.45,0:16:37.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to hear it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.59,0:16:40.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.91,0:16:42.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.24,0:16:43.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What about Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.82,0:16:46.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We absolutely can't let her stay here indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.93,0:16:48.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But she has a medical condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.86,0:16:51.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?\NAmnesia is a medical condition, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.59,0:16:53.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.99,0:16:59.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,However, her real parents have no way of knowing that\Nand are probably desperate to find her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.19,0:17:03.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the sooner we let her meet her parents,\Nthe sooner they'll be relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.60,0:17:06.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But how do we get in touch with those\Nwho might be looking for her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.53,0:17:09.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,With this. We'll put a notice in the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.61,0:17:11.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here, they have advertisement section.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.34,0:17:13.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is the one more conspicuous spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.30,0:17:16.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,where we could put a notification\Nof us keeping her in custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.69,0:17:18.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if her parents will really see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.72,0:17:22.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We can't know for sure. But perhaps,\Nit's not just her parents who are looking for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.28,0:17:24.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Be it a relative or just someone close...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.69,0:17:26.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Someone will definitely see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.73,0:17:28.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think about this plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.87,0:17:30.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's good I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.24,0:17:31.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sylvia, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.93,0:17:33.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that she's adorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.82,0:17:35.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But she's not {\i1}our{\i0} daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.72,0:17:36.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.29,0:17:40.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, come back, you guy! Come now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.37,0:17:44.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.79,0:17:45.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.98,0:17:51.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, my wife dotes on that child so much...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.52,0:17:52.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.10,0:18:15.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon.\NIs someone in the office?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.32,0:18:16.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.21,0:18:22.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. You see, I need to ask for a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.56,0:18:24.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be there in a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.20,0:18:30.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How may I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.20,0:18:37.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to post this notice in the advertisement section.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.01,0:18:39.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's ten shillings per word.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.06,0:18:42.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.\NThen, please post it in the tomorrow's issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.68,0:18:43.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.62,0:18:44.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.35,0:18:45.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.43,0:18:48.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is tomorrow's advertisement section filled up already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.51,0:18:52.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No-no, it's just that tomorrow is Sunday\Nso we won't have an issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.10,0:18:54.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... That's right, it's Saturday today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.60,0:18:57.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad. Then, the Monday's issue, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.20,0:19:01.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt.\N1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.10,0:19:06.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're finally going to Duke of York's mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.09,0:19:18.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Duke of York, huh?\NHe totally wouldn't know anything about Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.97,0:19:23.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A newspaper?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.70,0:19:26.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't know anything about Lucy either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.40,0:19:30.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, not necessarily!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.50,0:19:38.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.61,0:19:40.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.31,0:19:44.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to know something.\NHow much does it cost to post an ad in your paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.82,0:19:46.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What would you like to post?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.20,0:19:47.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A missing person notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.53,0:19:49.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be ten shillings per character.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.37,0:19:51.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ten Shillings?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.92,0:19:52.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.33,0:19:55.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.36,0:19:56.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.19,0:19:59.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You want to post a notice\Nabout a missing person, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.82,0:20:00.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.61,0:20:02.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I have to consult my family first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.89,0:20:05.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better apply for it as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.61,0:20:08.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The advertisement section tends to fill up in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.30,0:20:09.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.23,0:20:16.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A girl of about ten years of age,\Nwho lost her memory, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.82,0:20:19.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This goes in the "missing person" section.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.83,0:20:28.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, so lovely!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.63,0:20:34.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you... Are you giving this to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.66,0:20:36.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, it's yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.50,0:20:38.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.62,0:20:40.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, very much so!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.64,0:20:44.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm seeing a doll this lovely\Nfor the first time in my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.47,0:20:45.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, you did it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.54,0:20:46.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.45,0:20:50.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You need to remember your life up to this point\Nto be saying things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.10,0:20:52.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.52,0:20:56.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure it's true. Even if I can't remember\Nanything about my past,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.51,0:21:00.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's the first time I'm seeing a doll so wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.61,0:21:03.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad to see that I made you happy, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.66,0:21:06.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It caught my eye in a store I've been to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.59,0:21:08.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.97,0:21:10.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.70,0:21:18.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, how curious.\NProspero seems awfully jealous of this doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.03,0:21:20.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Prospero.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.50,0:21:26.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, it's my sister. Isn't she cute?\NYou shouldn't be mad at her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.80,0:21:34.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right! Do you understand it now?\NShe's my sister and her name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.88,0:21:38.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What name will you give her, Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.19,0:21:42.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.90,0:21:44.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just now, in my mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.35,0:21:47.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,a certain name suddenly popped up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.71,0:21:48.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What name?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.90,0:21:56.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember. But it's a very nostalgic name,\Nthe one I know very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.28,0:22:03.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure... I'm sure it used to be my own name.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.80,0:22:09.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.09,0:22:10.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.52,0:22:19.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sylvia, the Duke of York's wife\Nsaid she absolutely wants to meet Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.39,0:22:22.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my dear.\NYou already told her about Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.22,0:22:25.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. And the incident piqued her interest a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.40,0:22:27.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I told her she's an adorable child
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.32,0:22:29.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,and promised to bring her with me tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.79,0:22:31.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.99,0:22:36.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Emily, have you ever met the duchess?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.08,0:22:40.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. It was foolish of me to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.31,0:22:44.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't remember a thing from your past, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.76,0:22:51.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Each word costs ten shillings\Nso be sure to make it as short as possible, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.51,0:22:52.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.09,0:22:59.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When you're done writing that,\Nhave some tea before going to the publisher.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.95,0:23:01.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You've enough time for that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.40,0:23:08.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this should do, I reckon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.89,0:23:27.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, ten, missing - Popple.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.51,0:23:29.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This goes in the missing persons section, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.70,0:23:59.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy didn't return that day either.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.41,0:24:07.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I manage to regain my memory\Nthanks to a reunion with Little.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.18,0:24:10.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now I can return safely to my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.50,0:24:14.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"Little! Little!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.68,0:24:16.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
